<span id="freeTextContainer4353980350615372818">This is a fun and exciting book that is just a little bit scary for young readers but also reassuring. The ending is open-ended and can lead to many wonderful discussions about the bear and its behavior. The expressions and body language of the family and their pet dog are nicely done, with detail and feeling. The text flows and children readily participate in the story.</span>

