        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780689504761" href="/book/show/2213760.We_re_Going_on_a_Bear_Hunt">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/921817-heidi-marie?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/921817-heidi-marie?shelf=so-called-must-reads">so-called-must-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/921817-heidi-marie?shelf=preschool-storytime-read">preschool-storytime-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/921817-heidi-marie?shelf=fluff">fluff</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/921817-heidi-marie?shelf=picture-books">picture-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/921817-heidi-marie?shelf=children-0-12">children-0-12</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer45466093" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8896051539623098058">Well, it certainly isn&apos;t my version of a Bear Hunt, or even a Lion Hunt. I think there are hundreds of versions floating out there, and I can&apos;t help but be partial to my own. This one was hard for me to read since the words didn&apos;t quite go with the tune I know. Plus &quot;What a beautiful day!&quot; and then encountering a snowstorm? Not too much logic there. And the ending had some extra that I&apos;ve never heard before. I did enjoy the very, very end of that and had a laugh. The illustrations were nice. I&apos;m</span>
  <span id="freeText8896051539623098058" style="display:none">Well, it certainly isn't my version of a Bear Hunt, or even a Lion Hunt. I think there are hundreds of versions floating out there, and I can't help but be partial to my own. This one was hard for me to read since the words didn't quite go with the tune I know. Plus "What a beautiful day!" and then encountering a snowstorm? Not too much logic there. And the ending had some extra that I've never heard before. I did enjoy the very, very end of that and had a laugh. The illustrations were nice. I'm sure this is a great one for a story time and can get all the children participating, plus the pictures really do well in telling the story. But I didn't personally click with it. <br /><br />3/19/14 I'm trying to read books in storytime that I haven't before--stop going to my standard favorites. A bear theme presented itself, so I tried this. It was eh. They were into it. I know they liked the story. But I just couldn't get the text to work for me. But at least I tried. Next time it might be more fun to sing my own thing.</span>
